               <physDesc>
                  <objectDesc form="codex">
                     <supportDesc material="perg">
                        <support>
                           <p>
                              <material>Parchment.</material>
                           </p>
                        </support>
                        <extent>76. <dimensions type="leaf" scope="all">
                              <height unit="mm">315</height>
                              <width unit="mm">232</width>
                           </dimensions>.</extent>
                        <foliation>
                           <p>Foliated in red ink in the top outer corners. Traces of other
                              foliations.</p>
                        </foliation>
                        <condition>
                           <p>The manuscript ends defective and has various lacunae. Of fol. 71 only
                              a thin slip at the spine is left.</p>
                        </condition>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout columns="2" writtenLines="37 50">
                           <p>Written in two columns with 40 lines (fols <locus from="1ra" to="72ra"
                                 >1ra-72va</locus>), 37 to 40 lines (fols <locus from="72va"
                                 to="73vb">72va-73vb</locus>) and 44 to 50 lines (fols <locus
                                 from="74ra" to="76vb">74ra-76vb</locus>) per column.</p>
                        </layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <handDesc hands="3">
                     <handNote scope="major" script="unknown">
                        <p>Fols <locus from="1ra" to="72ra:2">1ra-72ra:2</locus> are written in a
                           hand from the end of the fourteenth century.</p>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote scope="minor" script="unknown">
                        <p>Fols <locus from="72ra" to="73vb">72ra-73vb</locus> are written in a hand
                           from c. 1500.</p>
                     </handNote>
                     <handNote scope="minor" script="unknown">
                        <p>Fols <locus from="74ra" to="76vb">74ra-76vb</locus> are written in a hand
                           from the sixteenth century.</p>
                     </handNote>
                  </handDesc>
                  <decoDesc>
                     <decoNote type="initial">
                        <p>The initials occur in varying colours. Rubrics in red.</p>
                     </decoNote>
                  </decoDesc>
                  <additions>
                     <p>
                        <name type="person" key="ArnMag001">Árni Magnússon</name> has marked some of
                        the lacunae in the bottom margin of the previous page. A number of
                        seventeenth-century notes in the lower margins of the codex provide
                        information of the manuscript's extent at the time (108 leaves). Also
                        written here and there in the margins are the names of various owners.</p>
                  </additions>
               </physDesc>
               <history>
                  <origin notBefore="1385" notAfter="1599" cert="high" evidence="external">
                     <p>The manuscript was written in <origPlace>Iceland</origPlace> in dates from
                           <origDate notBefore="1385" notAfter="15110">the end of the fourteenth
                           century and c. 1500</origDate>. <list>
                           <item>The main part of the manuscript, fols 1ra-72ra, containing <title
                                 type="uniform" xml:lang="is">Ólafs saga Tryggvasonar</title> dates
                              from the end of the fourteenth century but there are younger
                              additions. </item>
                           <item>Fols <locus from="72ra" to="73vb">72ra-73vb</locus> (<title
                                 type="uniform" xml:lang="is">Halldórs þáttr Snorrasonar</title>)
                              are from c.
                              1500.</item>
                           <item>Fols <locus from="74ra" to="76vb">74ra-76vb</locus> (<title>Excerpt
                                 from Ólafs saga Tryggvasonar</title>, <title>Nornagests
                                 þáttr</title> and <title type="uniform" xml:lang="is">Helga þáttr
                                 Þórissonar</title>) are from the sixteenth
                                 century and were intended as a supplement.</item>
                        </list>
                     </p>
                     <p>In <name type="person" key="ArnMag001">Árni Magnússon</name>'s time, the
                        beginning of the saga was written on some leaves of paper by <name
                           type="person" key="JonOla009">Jón Ólafsson</name> of <name type="place"
                           >Lambavatn</name> (<name type="place">Rauðasandur</name>) and added to
                        the manuscript. These were later removed and are now catalogued as <ref
                           type="ms" target="AM04-0325-IX-1-b-en">AM 325 IX 1 b 4to</ref>.</p>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance>
                     <p>According to <ref type="ms" target="#AM04-0435-a-en">AM 435 a 4to</ref>, fol. 37v, <name type="person"
                           key="ArnGud001">Árni Guðmundsson</name> of <name type="place"
                           >Bíldudalur</name> gave the manuscript to <name type="person"
                           key="ArnTho002">Arngrímur Þorkelsson</name>.</p>
                  </provenance>
                  <acquisition>
                     <p>
                        <name type="person" key="ArnMag001">Árni Magnússon</name> gives two
                        different accounts of how he got hold of the manuscript. On fol.
                           <locus>71r</locus> he writes that he got it from <name type="person"
                           key="MagAra001">Magnús Arason</name> in <date when="1703">1703</date> (<q
                           xml:lang="is">fra Magnuse Arasyne. 1703</q>).</p>
                     <p>In <ref type="ms" target="#AM04-0435-a-en">AM 435 a 4to</ref>, fol. 37v, however, he says that he got
                        the codex from <name type="person" key="ArnTho002">Arngrímur
                           Þorkelsson</name>: <q xml:lang="is">Olafs Saga Tryggvasonar, vantar i
                              hi<ex>er</ex>
                           <ex>og</ex> hv<ex>ar</ex> α <add place="opposite">α þar liggr i
                              Defectunum pappir med hendi Sr. Jons Olafs sonar  Lambavatne [now AM.
                              325 IX 1 b 4to]</add>. <lb/> Nornagests þattr. og <lb/> af Þorsteine
                           og Helga. Folio <pb/> Eg trui þesse bok kiæme af Vestfiỏdum <lb/> annad
                           hvert <hi rend="underline">t<ex>il</ex> Amtman<ex>n</ex>s Müllers</hi>
                           eda mïn. ad visu hefr þesse bok vered i hỏndum <lb/> Magnusar Jons sonar
                           i Vigr. þvi hans hỏnd <lb/> stendr  Spatiun<ex>n</ex>e i einum stad <lb/>
                           <add place="margin">
                              <foreign xml:lang="la">n<ex>on</ex> e<ex>st</ex> ita</foreign>
                              <lb/> Eg hefi <lb/> fei<ex>n</ex>gid bok<lb rend="hyphenated"/>ina af
                              Arngrimi <lb/> Þ<ex>or</ex>kels s<ex>yne</ex>
                              <lb/> enn han<ex>n</ex>
                              <lb/> fra Arna <lb/> Gudm<ex>un</ex>dz syne <lb/> i Billdu
                           dal</add>.</q>
                     </p>
                  </acquisition>
